                                <p>
                                    Dear Delegates,
                                </p>
                                <p>“Disarmament with mutual honor and confidence is a containing imperative. Together we must learn how to compose differences, not with arms, but with intellect and decent purpose.” - Dwight d Eisenhower</p>
                                <p>Dear delegates,</p>
                                <p>As the chairperson of The Disarmament and International Security Committee, it gives me great pleasure in welcoming all of you to The Doon School Model United Nations Conference 2016.</p>
                                <p>Before I talk about myself, let me tell you a little bit about the committee in general. The Disarmament and International Security Committee is The First Committee of the United Nations General Assembly. It deals with disarmament; global challenges and a threat to peace that affects the international community and seeks out solutions to the challenges in the international security regime. This committee will give you insights into the world of violence, destruction, devastation and economic turmoil and make you aware of the dangerous and unpredictable world that surrounds us. </p>
                                <p>As for myself, my primary interests lie in the sport of football (mind you not soccer), MUNing and studying (at least that’s what I tell my parents). I am a student of the International Baccalaureate and want to pursue business studies.  In committee I expect delegates to engage in active and productive debate and simultaneously enjoy DSMUN to the fullest. </p>
                                <p>This year, the agendas that will be discussed in DISEC are:</p>
                                <p><ul><li><b>Formulation of an international body for the military intervention in the ISIS issue.</b></li>
                                <li><b>International framework on the convention of air strikes and drone regulation.</b></li></ul></p>
                                <p>If any further aid is required all delegates are welcome to approach and contact me. Lastly, I expect the highest level of debate in hope to reach a plausible conclusion. Moreover I hope that all of you have a great time at Chandbagh.</p>
                                <div class="signing-off">
                                  <p class="line-height">Cheers,</p>
                                  <img src="/public/style/images/signs/yoye.png" width=160 height=120>
                                  <p class="line-height">Jayaditya Singh</p>
                                  <p class="line-height">Chairperson - DISEC</p>
                                  <p class="line-height">DSMUN '16</p>
                                </div>
