                        <div id="agenda-intro">
                          <h2>Introduction to Agenda</h2>
                          <div class="divide20"></div>
                          <h3>Agenda 1: Drone Regulation and Air Strikes</h3>
                          <p>The use of drones can and will have devastating consequences for the whole world.  Drones are dangerous simply because they are released at one place and attack a different place which cannot be controlled at the time of attack.</p>
                          <p>The use or rather the misuse of drones is fast becoming a severe threat to world population. Controlling the ever-growing nuclear arsenal of various countries and the excessive use of drones has become of paramount importance to the UN.</p>
                          <p>Our committee aims at finding a feasible alternative to drones and finding a solution to the predicament at hand so as to minimise the loss of human lives.</p>
                          <h3>Agenda 2: The Rise of Anomalous Warfare and Non State Actors</h3>
                          <p>The Islamic State (IS) needs no introduction. It is by far the biggest safety concern of the whole world. The freedom and the safety of the world are at stake and thus this automatically becomes the biggest issue for the UN to deal with.</p>
                          <p>Now that all attempts at finding a peaceful solution to the problem have failed, the only solution to tackle the issue will have to be through violent means.</p>
                          <p><b>Our committee aims at forming an international body which will carry out a feasible attack on the ISIS and aim to potentially save innumerable human lives.</b></p>

